<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head>
        <title>CSS Test: Negative value for blur radius</title>
        <link href="http://www.microsoft.com/" rel="author" title="Microsoft" />
        <link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-background/#the-box-shadow" rel="help" />
        <meta content="" name="flags" />
        <meta content="Negative values for the blur radius of the 'box-shadow' are not allowed." name="assert" />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                width: 1in;
                height: 1in;
                border: thin solid black;
                box-shadow: red 0 10px -10px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div></div>
    
</body></html>